text: Events from the year 1521 in Ireland. ==Events== * George Cromer (died 1543) was appointed (Church of Ireland) Archbishop of Armagh and Primate of All Ireland under Henry VIII. ==Births== ==Deaths== *29 November – William Rokeby, a leading statesman and cleric in the early sixteenth-century, who held the offices of Bishop of Meath, Archbishop of Dublin and Lord Chancellor of Ireland. ==References== Category:1520s in Ireland Ireland Category:Years of the 16th century in Ireland
title: 1521 in Ireland
